text.data-name: Labour markets are volatile, uncertain, complex, and ambiguous
Business wellbeing is prioritised over worker wellbeing making both the workers and businesses vulnerable
Low wages and no social security or coverage
Poor health, safety, security & productivity leading to poor livelihood opportunities, low self-esteem, absenteeism, high attrition and turnover which discourages investment in them.
Threatening the lives & livelihoods of workers experiencing precarious working conditions, poverty, low wages, illness, discrimination & violence.
